1999.analysis_summary: Subject demonstrates high latent potential. Primary activities involve basic biological functions and rapid sensory data acquisition.

2001.analysis_summary: Early cognitive development. Subject shows basic pattern recognition and response to auditory stimuli. Beginning to understand cause and effect relationships.

2002.analysis_summary: Language acquisition phase. Subject demonstrates improved communication skills and ability to express needs effectively. Social interaction patterns emerging with intentional communication replacing basic signals.

2003.analysis_summary: Pre-school transition phase. Subject experiencing new environments and social structures. Memory formation and emotional regulation developing. Demonstrates resilience in adapting to unfamiliar settings.

2004 - 2009.analysis_summary: Primary education phase. Subject demonstrates exceptional creative abilities through constant drawing, filling entire books. Strong interest in building and making things inspired by educational shows. Natural athleticism through sports participation. Early career aspiration toward software engineering despite no computer access, indicating strong forward-thinking logic. Exceptional social skills with easy friend-making abilities.

2010.analysis_summary: Consciousness awakening phase. Subject demonstrates self-directed learning and decision-making. First computer acquisition (Intel Dual-Core, 1GB RAM, 128GB HDD) marks beginning of technical journey. Immediate engagement with QBasic, HTML, and CSS through school curriculum. Strong gaming interest across multiple platforms. Natural affinity for technology and programming concepts detected.

2011.analysis_summary: Digital world entry phase. Subject demonstrates proactive learning to overcome FOMO from missed opportunities. Self-directed learning of Google SketchUp and arts & crafts. Strong collaborative skills working with peers. Shows initiative in catching up on missed content independently.

2012.analysis_summary: Programming proficiency emerging. Subject demonstrates strong logical thinking and problem-solving abilities through C and C++ curriculum. Deep fascination with coding. Strong experimental mindset exploring YouTube experiments (free energy concepts, robot building). Interest in systems understanding, game modding, and reverse engineering concepts. Natural curiosity for technical boundaries.

2013.analysis_summary: Learning obsession phase. Subject demonstrates exceptional ability to learn diverse skills rapidly to overcome FOMO. Mastery of After Effects (influenced by Andrew Kramer), CrazyTalk Animator, and Photoshop. Collaborative filmmaking projects with friends. Introduction to electronics at school. Strong creative technology intersection. Multidisciplinary learning approach evident.

2014.analysis_summary: High school transition with expanded technical interests. Subject demonstrates paradigm shift in understanding physics and the world through self-directed reading beyond curriculum. Deep engagement with MAKE magazine. Significant electronics expertise developing through hands-on projects: LEDs, motors, toy cars, toothbrush bots, rubber band guns. Natural teaching and showcasing abilities. Strong maker mindset.

2015.analysis_summary: The hacker phase. Subject demonstrates exceptional Java proficiency with strong OOP understanding. Built 'Brigade OS' (specialized application). Introduction to cybersecurity concepts through 'Hacking for Dummies': VMs, Kali Linux, ethical hacking (phishing, XSS). Content creation pivot: YouTube channel 'Neutrino' transitioned from Rubik's Cube solves to Java tutorials. Strong technical communication skills emerging.

2016.analysis_summary: End of high school phase. Subject demonstrates deep understanding of physics and chemistry, successfully applying scientific principles to technology. Strong interest in 3D graphics and game development: learned Blender, Cinema4D, and Unity. Built 'Office Run' (2D jetpack game) and 'Santa's Lost Hat' (3D platformer). Passion for world-building and game creation evident.

2017.analysis_summary: Pre-university phase. Subject demonstrates advanced self-directed learning through 'The Coding Train' binge-watching. Strong interest in physics simulations using P5.js. Built first neural network for handwriting recognition, showing early AI/ML interest. Deep technical dive into electronics: transducers, silicon, digital vs. analog circuits. Significant theoretical and practical electronics knowledge.

2018.analysis_summary: The maker year. Subject demonstrates exceptional hands-on skills: hand-soldered digital clock without microcontroller (demonstrating deep electronics understanding). Massive Arduino project portfolio: 20-30 projects including scientific calculators and drones. College exhibition provided focus for practical learning. Strong maker/DIY ethos with production-level project execution.

2019.analysis_summary: Engineering & first internship phase. Subject demonstrates career clarity through experimentation: video editing internship revealed non-fit, leading to pivot. Strong hackathon performance winning paid internship in medical devices and EVs. Found professional community alignment. Shows ability to quickly assess fit and pivot strategically.

2020.analysis_summary: Lockdown & viral fame phase. Subject demonstrates entrepreneurial initiative: launched Arduino course, worked at token management startup, built React Native app. Collegiate Go-Kart racing team participation. Viral calculator hack video featured on VICE and international news, opening global freelancing opportunities. Strong content creation and technical communication skills. Multi-project execution capability.

2021.analysis_summary: Going global phase. Subject demonstrates international client work capability: GPS voice assistant for Danish client, acoustic device for Brazilian company. Significant open-source contributions around MP3 players. Industrial design studio internship secured through open-source work. Strong global collaboration and technical communication skills. Professional-grade project delivery.

2022.analysis_summary: Final year of engineering phase. Subject demonstrates professional multitasking: design studio work while completing classes. Learned mass manufacturing and industrial design principles. Academic excellence: published two IEEE papers, secured patents. Community leadership: hosted workshops across Bangalore. Launched PCBCupid as Q&A site. Personal development: achieved 1200 ELO on Chess.com. Strong research, teaching, and entrepreneurial capabilities.

2023.analysis_summary: Job to exploration phase. Subject demonstrates entrepreneurial courage: quit job in Q1 to go solo. Pivoted PCBCupid into YouTube channel and hired interns. Life-changing train travel across India with 800 strangers, learning entrepreneurship and funding. Won hardware contests. High-level consulting: high-speed electronics and Embedded Linux. Personal milestone: learned to swim. Strong risk-taking, leadership, and technical expertise.

2024.analysis_summary: PCBCupid company phase. Subject demonstrates business execution: officially registered PCBCupid as company on Valentine's Day. Goal: build India's largest hardware community. Product launch: collaborated with LionCircuits to launch GLYPH (affordable ESP32 board). B2B sales growth. Advanced technical skills: Zephyr RTOS, high-speed design. Professional development: attended Microchip Masters for EMI/EMC expertise. Strong technical depth and business acumen.

2025.analysis_summary: Scaling up phase. Subject demonstrates organizational growth: team expansion, PCBCupid becoming trusted vendor for multiple companies. Strong community leadership: hosting 'Founder Mode' events and two successful hackathons. Strategic networking: FOSSIndia 2025 participation brought partnerships and expanded hardware circle significantly. Strong social and business development skills alongside technical expertise.

2026.analysis_summary: Beyond & beyond phase. Subject is positioned for continued growth and expansion. Next chapter loading with strong foundation in hardware engineering, entrepreneurship, community building, and technical leadership. Operating at peak capacity across multiple dimensions.
